 is not re-resolved from `resolveTranscriptPath()` \\n3. Therefore, when condensation tries to read the live transcript, it uses the stale path\\n\\n### **Solution Approach**\\n\\nThe fix requires **re-resolving the TranscriptPath dynamically** before each condensation in the PostCommit hook, rather than relying on the cached value in session state.\\n\\nSpecifically, in `PostCommit()` before calling `CondenseSession()`, the code should:\\n1. Load the session state from disk\\n2. Re-resolve the `TranscriptPath` using `resolveTranscriptPath(sessionID, agent)` \\n3. Update the session state's `TranscriptPath` if it differs\\n4. Use the fresh path for condensation\\n\\nOr more directly, `CondenseSession()` could accept an optional parameter to re-compute the transcript path dynamically, or the caller should ensure the transcript path is current before calling it.\\n\\nThis aligns with the existing design principle noted in `manual_commit_condensation.go` line 363:\\n> \\\"transcript paths are always computed dynamically from the current repo location (via `agent.GetSessionDir` + `agent.ResolveSessionFile`), never stored in checkpoint metadata. This ensures restore/rewind works after repo relocation or across machines.\\\"\\n\\nHowever, the **session state itself is storing the transcript path**, which becomes stale between commits.\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a78135e (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 118337\\ntool_uses: 31\\nduration_ms: 104084</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"927a5109-60d9-4e59-90cb-21c5e135fe45\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-21T00:20:06.415Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"I need to understand why the second commit in a multi-commit E2E test scenario doesn't have transcripts on `entire/checkpoints/v1`.\\n\\nThe pattern across multiple failing tests:\\n- A single agent prompt creates files\\n- First `GitCommitWithShadowHooks` creates a checkpoint and transcript appears on `entire