pointTranscriptStart` updated to the total transcript lines (line 830 in manual_commit_hooks.go), but `TranscriptPath` is not re-resolved\\n\\n#### **The Root Cause in Context**\\n\\nLooking at `manual_commit_session.go` line 1433-1434:\\n```go\\nif transcriptPath != \\\"\\\" && state.TranscriptPath != transcriptPath {\\n    state.TranscriptPath = transcriptPath\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis update happens only during `InitializeSession` when a new `transcriptPath` parameter is passed. But after the first condensation, when the second commit's post-commit hook executes:\\n\\n1. No `transcriptPath` is passed (it comes from the Hook Input which may be outdated)\\n2. The session state's `TranscriptPath` is not re-resolved from `resolveTranscriptPath()` \\n3. Therefore, when condensation tries to read the live transcript, it uses the stale path\\n\\n### **Solution Approach**\\n\\nThe fix requires **re-resolving the TranscriptPath dynamically** before each condensation in the PostCommit hook, rather than relying on the cached value in session state.\\n\\nSpecifically, in `PostCommit()` before calling `CondenseSession()`, the code should:\\n1. Load the session state from disk\\n2. Re-resolve the `TranscriptPath` using `resolveTranscriptPath(sessionID, agent)` \\n3. Update the session state's `TranscriptPath` if it differs\\n4. Use the fresh path for condensation\\n\\nOr more directly, `CondenseSession()` could accept an optional parameter to re-compute the transcript path dynamically, or the caller should ensure the transcript path is current before calling it.\\n\\nThis aligns with the existing design principle noted in `manual_commit_condensation.go` line 363:\\n> \\\"transcript paths are always computed dynamically from the current repo location (via `agent.GetSessionDir` + `agent.ResolveSessionFile`), never stored in checkpoint metadata. This ensures restore/rewind works after repo relocation or across machines.\\\"\\n\\nHowever, the **session state itself is storing the transcript path**, which becomes stale between commits.\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":104084,\"totalTokens\":118337,\"totalToolUseCount\":31,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":586,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":116528,\"output_tokens\":1223,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":586,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"fb6b8f24-ce5b-4145-822d-54298dfd4d5a\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"927a5109-60d9-4e59-90cb-21c5e135fe45\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent\",\"sessionId\":\"9db38e1f-2859-40ee-b90b-0d17fc3fe360\",\"version\":\"2.1.49\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"parsed-hopping-sutton\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_018TrbHsrxNcYqTPnGq51bC5\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/factoryaidroid.go:99:\\traw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[sessionInfoRaw](r)\\n/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks.go:23:\\tHookNameStop             = \\\"stop\\\"\\n/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/hooks.go:45:\\t\\tHookNameStop,\\n/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/lifecycle.go:35:\\tcase HookNameStop:\\n/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/lifecycle.go:144:\\traw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[sessionInfoRaw](stdin)\\n/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent/cmd/entire/cli/agent/factoryaidroid/lifecycle.go:171:\\traw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[sessionInfoRaw](stdin)\\n/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent/cmd/entire/cl